The paper proposes a genetic approach for searching neural network structures from scratch, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). The approach also involves the use of mimicry and gene duplication, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the approach on image classification tasks (CIFAR-100 dataset), which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves optimizing the performance of the neural network, which is a common goal in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the approach involves the use of evolutionary algorithms, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
